issue.title: [FEATURE REQUEST] Allow to replace golog dependency
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I would like to have only on logger in  my project, and I'm unable to replace golog in iris. 
I know I can integrate external loggers in golog but I only get a string message already processed, no message arguments or stacktrace to report in the external logger as I want.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Iris should use an interface that anyone can implement with all loggers.

issue.title: How Can I Get Websocket Timeout Err Message Or Event

comment.body:
Hello @fanglina, thank YOU for using it.

> Sorry for the late response.

You should receive websocket connection errors on the `OnUpgradeError` listener and inside all event listeners accepting the `websocket.Message` instance, which holds the `Err` field. After that you can check if the provided error's type is a timeout error. Iris provides the `isCanceled := iris.IsErrCanceled(err)` which you can use directly or copy its code to your own utility source file.

Please reply if the suggested solution works for you or we should implement something else for this case.

issue.title: [FEATURE REQUEST] Allow to replace golog dependency
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I would like to have only on logger in  my project, and I'm unable to replace golog in iris. 
I know I can integrate external loggers in golog but I only get a string message already processed, no message arguments or stacktrace to report in the external logger as I want.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Iris should use an interface that anyone can implement with all loggers.

package main

import (

)

func main() {
	irisApp := iris.Default()
	irisApp.Logger().SetLevel(logrus.DebugLevel.String())

	irisApp.Get("/api/v1/test/{echo:uint64}", func(context iris.Context) {
		_, _ = context.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("echo is %d", context.Params().GetUint64Default("echo", 0)))
	})

	irisApp.Get("/api/v1/test/{echo:uint64}", func(context iris.Context) {
		_, _ = context.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("echo 123 is %d", context.Params().GetUint64Default("echo", 0)))

issue.title: How to Graceful Restart the iris project ???
issue.body:
How to Graceful Restart the iris project ???
i know how to graceful restart gin project (use endless)  but not iris

comment.body:
Hello @weijchun,

Whatever works for gin and net/http works for Iris too. 

Take for example, the [endless](https://github.com/fvbock/endless) package you mentioned, it wants an `http.Handler (mux)` on its `endless.ListenAndServe("localhost:4242", mux)` function.

The `app := iris.New()` returns an `*iris.Application` instance, the `*iris.Application` completes the `http.Handler` interface and it's ready to use after `app.Build()`. With Iris, when not calling its `.Listen or .Run` and want to use it as a simple `http.Handler` directly, you need to call its "Build" method because there are many features compared to its alternatives that must be built when routing code is finish. Here's an example of your use case:

```go
app := iris.New()
app.Get("/", func(ctx iris.Context) { ctx.Writef("Hello %s", "Iris") }

if err := app.Build(); err!=nil { // <-
    panic(err)
}

err := endless.ListenAndServe("localhost:4242", app)
```

Simple as that! Have fun!

comment.body:
You can't do this, Application's RegisterView should be called before Listen (= no after build).

You can set multiple view engines [path-based](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L17) or [manually](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L23-L29).

You should not load and render the templates each time dynamically, this will make your app a lot slower. Explain us the problem and we may find a better solution. Also, do the templates written in the disk before server ran or your users upload multiple template files on the fly?

comment.body:
You can't do this, Application's RegisterView should be called before Listen (= no after build).

You can set multiple view engines [path-based](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L17) or [manually](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L23-L29).

You should not load and render the templates each time dynamically, this will make your app a lot slower. Explain us the problem and we may find a better solution.

issue.title: [BUG] Iris server crash with StackOverflow when changing ResponseWriter
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
The Iris server crashes when I attempt to add a NewRelic middleware.

**To Reproduce**
Here is a lightweight reproducible example
```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"net/http"

	"github.com/kataras/golog"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/context"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/middleware/logger"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/middleware/recover"

         "github.com/iris-contrib/middleware/newrelic"
	NR "github.com/newrelic/go-agent/v3/newrelic"
)

func main() {
	app := iris.New()

	// Global middlewares
	app.UseGlobal(recover.New())
	app.UseGlobal(logger.New())
	app.UseGlobal(createNewRelicMiddleware(app.Logger()))

	// Router
	app.Get("/test", test)

	// Start server
	app.Listen(":8080")
}

func test(ctx iris.Context) {
	ctx.Text("Hello world")
}

func createNewRelicMiddleware(logger *golog.Logger) context.Handler {
         appName := "my-app"
	 licenseKey := "enter_key_here"
	// New Relic initialization
	middleware, err := newrelic.New(
		NR.ConfigAppName(appName),
		NR.ConfigLicense(licenseKey),
		NR.ConfigDistributedTracerEnabled(true),
	)
	if err != nil {
		fmt.Println(err)
		logger.Fatal(err)
	}
	return middleware
}
```

**Expected behavior**
Being able to see "Hello World" when I make the HTTP GET request.

**Screenshots**

github.com/kataras/iris/v12/context.(*responseWriter).Header(0x0?)

pull_request.body:
Bumps [github.com/kataras/golog](https://github.com/kataras/golog) from 0.1.7 to 0.1.8.
Release notes

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's releases.

v0.1.8

What's Changed

  • Add func for GetNameForLevel by @​codenamoo in kataras/golog#8
  • copy NewLine value as well when clone logger by @​JayceChant in kataras/golog#9
  • Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 by @​dependabot in kataras/golog#23

New Contributors

  • @​codenamoo made their first contribution in kataras/golog#8
  • @​JayceChant made their first contribution in kataras/golog#9
  • @​dependabot made their first contribution in kataras/golog#23

Full Changelog: https://github.com/kataras/golog/compare/v0.1.7...v0.1.8

Changelog

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's changelog.

Sat 29 October 2022 | v0.1.8

Add golog.Now variable so 3rd-parties can customize the time.Now functionality used in golog.Log.Time and Timestamp.

Wed 09 Decemember | v0.1.6

Fix Clone not inherite the parent's formatters field (fixes SetLevelFormat on childs).

Mo 07 September | v0.1.5

Introduce the Formatter interface. Example.

  • Add Logger.RegisterFormatter(Formatter) to register a custom Formatter.
  • Add Logger.SetFormat(formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to set the default formatter for all log levels.
  • Add Logger.SetLevelFormat(levelName string, formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to change the output format for the given "levelName".

Su 06 September | v0.1.3 and v0.1.4

  • Add Logger.SetLevelOutput(levelName string, w io.Writer) to customize the writer per level.
  • Add Logger.GetLevelOutput(levelName string) io.Writer to get the leveled output or the default one.

Sa 15 August | v0.1.2

  • Logger.Child accepts an interface{} instead of string. This way you can register children for pointers without forcing to naming them. If the key is string or completes the fmt.Stringer interface, then it's used as prefix (like always did).

Fr 14 August 2020 | v0.0.19

  • Use locks on hijacker.

Tu 09 June 2020 | v0.0.18

  • New SetStacktraceLimit method. If 0 (default) all debug stacktrace will be logged, if negative the field is disabled.
  • If TimeFormat field is empty then timestamp field is disabled.

Sa 06 June 2020 | v0.0.16

  • New Fields type that can be passed to Logf/Debugf/Infof/Warnf/Errorf/Fatalf functions and set the Log.Fields data field (which can be retrieved through a custom LogHandler).
  • Add Log.Stacktrace of new Frame type which holds the callers stack trace when Debug/Debugf.
  • Add json struct fields to the Log structure.
  • Update the customize-output example.

Su 17 May 2020 | v0.0.14

Add a Warningf method to complete the dgraph-io/badger.Logger interface and set the Prefix text right before the log's actual message instead of the beginning of the log line.

Tu 28 April 2020 | v0.0.12

This release provides support for colorized log level per registered output. Log's level will be colorful for registered io.Writer(via AddOutput) that supports colors, even when the rest of the writers (e.g. files) don't.

Breaking changes on the Levels map. See the corresponding updated example for migration.

... (truncated)

pull_request.body:
Bumps [github.com/kataras/golog](https://github.com/kataras/golog) from 0.1.7 to 0.1.8.
Release notes

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's releases.

v0.1.8

What's Changed

  • Add func for GetNameForLevel by @​codenamoo in kataras/golog#8
  • copy NewLine value as well when clone logger by @​JayceChant in kataras/golog#9
  • Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 by @​dependabot in kataras/golog#23

New Contributors

  • @​codenamoo made their first contribution in kataras/golog#8
  • @​JayceChant made their first contribution in kataras/golog#9
  • @​dependabot made their first contribution in kataras/golog#23

Full Changelog: https://github.com/kataras/golog/compare/v0.1.7...v0.1.8

Changelog

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's changelog.

Sat 29 October 2022 | v0.1.8

Add golog.Now variable so 3rd-parties can customize the time.Now functionality used in golog.Log.Time and Timestamp.

Wed 09 Decemember | v0.1.6

Fix Clone not inherite the parent's formatters field (fixes SetLevelFormat on childs).

Mo 07 September | v0.1.5

Introduce the Formatter interface. Example.

  • Add Logger.RegisterFormatter(Formatter) to register a custom Formatter.
  • Add Logger.SetFormat(formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to set the default formatter for all log levels.
  • Add Logger.SetLevelFormat(levelName string, formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to change the output format for the given "levelName".

Su 06 September | v0.1.3 and v0.1.4

  • Add Logger.SetLevelOutput(levelName string, w io.Writer) to customize the writer per level.
  • Add Logger.GetLevelOutput(levelName string) io.Writer to get the leveled output or the default one.

Sa 15 August | v0.1.2

  • Logger.Child accepts an interface{} instead of string. This way you can register children for pointers without forcing to naming them. If the key is string or completes the fmt.Stringer interface, then it's used as prefix (like always did).

Fr 14 August 2020 | v0.0.19

  • Use locks on hijacker.

Tu 09 June 2020 | v0.0.18

  • New SetStacktraceLimit method. If 0 (default) all debug stacktrace will be logged, if negative the field is disabled.
  • If TimeFormat field is empty then timestamp field is disabled.

Sa 06 June 2020 | v0.0.16

  • New Fields type that can be passed to Logf/Debugf/Infof/Warnf/Errorf/Fatalf functions and set the Log.Fields data field (which can be retrieved through a custom LogHandler).
  • Add Log.Stacktrace of new Frame type which holds the callers stack trace when Debug/Debugf.
  • Add json struct fields to the Log structure.
  • Update the customize-output example.

Su 17 May 2020 | v0.0.14

Add a Warningf method to complete the dgraph-io/badger.Logger interface and set the Prefix text right before the log's actual message instead of the beginning of the log line.

Tu 28 April 2020 | v0.0.12

This release provides support for colorized log level per registered output. Log's level will be colorful for registered io.Writer(via AddOutput) that supports colors, even when the rest of the writers (e.g. files) don't.

Breaking changes on the Levels map. See the corresponding updated example for migration.

... (truncated)

  • 350ad62 Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 (#23)

issue.title: How Can I Get Websocket Timeout Err Message Or Event

comment.body:
Hello @fanglina, thank YOU for using it.

> Sorry for the late response.

You should receive websocket connection errors on the `OnUpgradeError` listener and inside all event listeners accepting the `websocket.Message` instance, which holds the `Err` field. After that you can check if the provided error's type is a timeout error. Iris provides the `isCanceled := iris.IsErrCanceled(err)` which you can use directly or copy its code to your own utility source file.

Please reply if the suggested solution works for you or we should implement something else for this case.

comment.body: It's not a good practise to re-build your templates each time a user applies a theme on the fly. You can do that using a single template which will be flexibile enough to apply any user theme you provide to your users, just like hugo does.

issue.title: [FEATURE REQUEST] Allow to replace golog dependency
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I would like to have only on logger in  my project, and I'm unable to replace golog in iris. 
I know I can integrate external loggers in golog but I only get a string message already processed, no message arguments or stacktrace to report in the external logger as I want.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Iris should use an interface that anyone can implement with all loggers.

comment.body:
I am not getting it, all of the features you mention already exist in `golog` (fatal and information of the app in general) or middleware/[accesslog](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/master/_examples/logging/request-logger/accesslog-simple/main.go) (http). With `golog` you can put message and arguments (= [golog.Fields](https://github.com/kataras/golog/blob/cab8303b290e6111eaf9669d59c31768e747cbed/_examples/customize-output/main.go#L52)). For request id you can use the `middleware/requestid` and get the id through `ctx.GetID()`.

Could you please provide an example of all the features you mentioned ?

issue.title: [BUG] route override with path parameters return 404
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When I override route with path parameters, it reports not found. Does it a bug?

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. the code look like below:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12"
	"github.com/sirupsen/logrus"
)

func main() {
	irisApp := iris.Default()
	irisApp.Logger().SetLevel(logrus.DebugLevel.String())

	irisApp.Get("/api/v1/test/{echo:uint64}", func(context iris.Context) {
		_, _ = context.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("echo is %d", context.Params().GetUint64Default("echo", 0)))
	})

	irisApp.Get("/api/v1/test/{echo:uint64}", func(context iris.Context) {
		_, _ = context.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("echo 123 is %d", context.Params().GetUint64Default("echo", 0)))
	})

	if err := irisApp.Run(iris.Addr(":8080"), iris.WithCharset("UTF-8")); err != nil {
		logrus.Errorf("error with :%+v", err)
	}
}
```
2. when I use postman to visit 'http://localhost:8080/api/v1/test/123' , it returns 404.

**Expected behavior**
when I visit http://localhost:8080/api/v1/test/123, it should be returns `echo 123 is 123`

**Screenshots**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22853384/203600244-0793c48e-0575-4c70-b4b9-417e35f49bf9.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22853384/203600158-51b9dea9-643b-4044-aac5-8d93cc6dc83c.png)

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: windows or ubuntu

**iris.Version**
- e.g. v12.2.0-beta6

issue.title: [BUG] ctx.RemoteAddr() incorrect for multiple IP addresses
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
ctx.RemoteAddr() method results in incorrect value when parsing X-Forwarded-For header which has multiple IP addresses.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/core/netutil"
	"strings"
)


func main() {
	ipAddresses := strings.Split("1.1.1.1, 8.8.8.8, 192.168.88.1", ",")
	fmt.Println(netutil.GetIPAddress(ipAddresses, []netutil.IPRange{
		{Start: "8.8.8.8", End: "8.8.8.8"},
		{Start: "192.168.0.0", End: "192.168.255.255"},
	}))
}
```
stdout:
```
192.168.88.1 true
```

**Expected behavior**
Returns non-excluded ip address. In above case should be `1.1.1.1`

**Screenshots**
If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: linux & mac m1

**iris.Version**
- v12.2.0-beta6

issue.title: How to Graceful Restart the iris project ???
issue.body:
How to Graceful Restart the iris project ???
i know how to graceful restart gin project (use endless)  but not iris

comment.body:
Hello @weijchun,

Whatever works for gin and net/http works for Iris too. 

Take for example, the [endless](https://github.com/fvbock/endless) package you mentioned, it wants an `http.Handler (mux)` on its `endless.ListenAndServe("localhost:4242", mux)` function.

The `app := iris.New()` returns an `*iris.Application` instance, the `*iris.Application` completes the `http.Handler` interface and it's ready to use after `app.Build()`. With Iris, when not calling its `.Listen or .Run` and want to use it as a simple `http.Handler` directly, you need to call its "Build" method because there are many features compared to its alternatives that must be built when routing code is finish. Here's an example of your use case:

```go
app := iris.New()
app.Get("/", func(ctx iris.Context) { ctx.Writef("Hello %s", "Iris") }

if err := app.Build(); err!=nil { // <-
    panic(err)
}

err := endless.ListenAndServe("localhost:4242", app)
```

Simple as that! Have fun!

func (c *ActionController) BeforeActivation(b mvc.BeforeActivation) {

}

func (c *ActionController) ChangeTheme() {
	name := c.Ctx.Params().Get("name")

	datasource.GetEngine().RegisterView(tmp)
	c.Ctx.Text("modify theme success")
}

how to change view.HTMLEngine dynamically ?

What should I do ?

thank you very much

comment.body:
You can't do this, Application's RegisterView should be called before Listen (= no after build).

You can set multiple view engines [path-based](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L17) or [manually](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L23-L29).

You should not load and render the templates each time dynamically, this will make your app a lot slower. Explain us the problem and we may find a better solution. Also, do the templates written in the disk before server ran or your users upload multiple template files on the fly?

issue.title: [BUG] Iris server crash with StackOverflow when changing ResponseWriter
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
The Iris server crashes when I attempt to add a NewRelic middleware.

**To Reproduce**
Here is a lightweight reproducible example
```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"net/http"

	"github.com/kataras/golog"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/context"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/middleware/logger"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/middleware/recover"

         "github.com/iris-contrib/middleware/newrelic"
	NR "github.com/newrelic/go-agent/v3/newrelic"
)

func main() {
	app := iris.New()

	// Global middlewares
	app.UseGlobal(recover.New())
	app.UseGlobal(logger.New())
	app.UseGlobal(createNewRelicMiddleware(app.Logger()))

	// Router
	app.Get("/test", test)

	// Start server
	app.Listen(":8080")
}

func test(ctx iris.Context) {
	ctx.Text("Hello world")
}

func createNewRelicMiddleware(logger *golog.Logger) context.Handler {
         appName := "my-app"
	 licenseKey := "enter_key_here"
	// New Relic initialization
	middleware, err := newrelic.New(
		NR.ConfigAppName(appName),
		NR.ConfigLicense(licenseKey),
		NR.ConfigDistributedTracerEnabled(true),
	)
	if err != nil {
		fmt.Println(err)
		logger.Fatal(err)
	}
	return middleware
}
```

**Expected behavior**
Being able to see "Hello World" when I make the HTTP GET request.

**Screenshots**
Here is the console logs 
```
Iris Version:   12.2.0-beta5
Build Time:     2022-11-09T01:37:49Z
Build Revision: c03f18d38ce18d50881a205d0313038bd8519183

Now listening on: http://localhost:8080
Application started. Press CTRL+C to shut down.
runtime: goroutine stack exceeds 1000000000-byte limit
runtime: sp=0xc020680388 stack=[0xc020680000, 0xc040680000]
fatal error: stack overflow

runtime stack:
runtime.throw({0x1b366cd?, 0x22df540?})
        /usr/local/go/src/runtime/panic.go:1047 +0x5d fp=0x2069f3d80 sp=0x2069f3d50 pc=0x103725d
runtime.newstack()
        /usr/local/go/src/runtime/stack.go:1103 +0x5cc fp=0x2069f3f38 sp=0x2069f3d80 pc=0x105082c
runtime.morestack()
        /usr/local/go/src/runtime/asm_amd64.s:570 +0x8b fp=0x2069f3f40 sp=0x2069f3f38 pc=0x106636b

goroutine 33 [running]:
go.(*struct { net/http.ResponseWriter; net/http.Flusher; net/http.Hijacker }).Header(0xc000292540?)
        <autogenerated>:1 +0x3e fp=0xc020680398 sp=0xc020680390 pc=0x193883e
github.com/kataras/iris/v12/context.(*responseWriter).Header(0x0?)
        <autogenerated>:1 +0x2a fp=0xc0206803b0 sp=0xc020680398 pc=0x1589caa
github.com/newrelic/go-agent/v3/newrelic.(*replacementResponseWriter).Header(0x0?)
        /Users/vkapuku/programming/go/src/messaging-service/vendor/github.com/newrelic/go-agent/v3/newrelic/internal_response_writer.go:19 +0x22 fp=0xc0206803c8 sp=0xc0206803b0 pc=0x19084a2
go.(*struct { net/http.ResponseWriter; net/http.Flusher; net/http.Hijacker }).Header(0x0?)
```

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: MacOS Monterey 12.5.1
- Golang 1.19.2 darwin/amd64

**iris.Version**
- e.g. v12.2.0-beta5 or master

Please make sure the bug is reproducible over the `master` branch:


```sh
$ cd PROJECT
$ go get -u github.com/kataras/iris/v12@master
$ go run .
```
^ I just did this and it still fails with the same error.

Furthermore, I made a local copy of the community `newrelic` middleware to debug it, and I noticed that the line which causes this failure is [this one](https://github.com/iris-contrib/middleware/blob/master/newrelic/newrelic.go#L66):

```go
ctx.ResponseWriter().SetWriter(txnWriter)
```

Commenting out this line will solve the issue

comment.body:
Hello @FrenchMajesty,

I've just updated the middleware, could you please try:

```sh
go get github.com/kataras/iris/v12@master
go get github.com/iris-contrib/middleware/newrelic@master
```

And let me know?

Thanks,
Gerasimos Maropoulos

pull_request.body:
Bumps [github.com/kataras/golog](https://github.com/kataras/golog) from 0.1.7 to 0.1.8.
Release notes

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's releases.

v0.1.8

What's Changed

  • Add func for GetNameForLevel by @​codenamoo in kataras/golog#8
  • copy NewLine value as well when clone logger by @​JayceChant in kataras/golog#9
  • Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 by @​dependabot in kataras/golog#23

New Contributors

  • @​codenamoo made their first contribution in kataras/golog#8
  • @​JayceChant made their first contribution in kataras/golog#9
  • @​dependabot made their first contribution in kataras/golog#23

Full Changelog: https://github.com/kataras/golog/compare/v0.1.7...v0.1.8

Changelog

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's changelog.

Sat 29 October 2022 | v0.1.8

Add golog.Now variable so 3rd-parties can customize the time.Now functionality used in golog.Log.Time and Timestamp.

Wed 09 Decemember | v0.1.6

Fix Clone not inherite the parent's formatters field (fixes SetLevelFormat on childs).

Mo 07 September | v0.1.5

Introduce the Formatter interface. Example.

  • Add Logger.RegisterFormatter(Formatter) to register a custom Formatter.
  • Add Logger.SetFormat(formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to set the default formatter for all log levels.
  • Add Logger.SetLevelFormat(levelName string, formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to change the output format for the given "levelName".

Su 06 September | v0.1.3 and v0.1.4

  • Add Logger.SetLevelOutput(levelName string, w io.Writer) to customize the writer per level.
  • Add Logger.GetLevelOutput(levelName string) io.Writer to get the leveled output or the default one.

Sa 15 August | v0.1.2

  • Logger.Child accepts an interface{} instead of string. This way you can register children for pointers without forcing to naming them. If the key is string or completes the fmt.Stringer interface, then it's used as prefix (like always did).

Fr 14 August 2020 | v0.0.19

  • Use locks on hijacker.

Tu 09 June 2020 | v0.0.18

  • New SetStacktraceLimit method. If 0 (default) all debug stacktrace will be logged, if negative the field is disabled.
  • If TimeFormat field is empty then timestamp field is disabled.

Sa 06 June 2020 | v0.0.16

  • New Fields type that can be passed to Logf/Debugf/Infof/Warnf/Errorf/Fatalf functions and set the Log.Fields data field (which can be retrieved through a custom LogHandler).
  • Add Log.Stacktrace of new Frame type which holds the callers stack trace when Debug/Debugf.
  • Add json struct fields to the Log structure.
  • Update the customize-output example.

Su 17 May 2020 | v0.0.14

Add a Warningf method to complete the dgraph-io/badger.Logger interface and set the Prefix text right before the log's actual message instead of the beginning of the log line.

Tu 28 April 2020 | v0.0.12

This release provides support for colorized log level per registered output. Log's level will be colorful for registered io.Writer(via AddOutput) that supports colors, even when the rest of the writers (e.g. files) don't.

Breaking changes on the Levels map. See the corresponding updated example for migration.

... (truncated)

issue.title: How Can I Get Websocket Timeout Err Message Or Event

comment.body:
Hello @fanglina, thank YOU for using it.

> Sorry for the late response.

You should receive websocket connection errors on the `OnUpgradeError` listener and inside all event listeners accepting the `websocket.Message` instance, which holds the `Err` field. After that you can check if the provided error's type is a timeout error. Iris provides the `isCanceled := iris.IsErrCanceled(err)` which you can use directly or copy its code to your own utility source file.

Please reply if the suggested solution works for you or we should implement something else for this case.

issue.title: [BUG] route override with path parameters return 404
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When I override route with path parameters, it reports not found. Does it a bug?

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. the code look like below:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12"
	"github.com/sirupsen/logrus"
)

func main() {
	irisApp := iris.Default()
	irisApp.Logger().SetLevel(logrus.DebugLevel.String())

	irisApp.Get("/api/v1/test/{echo:uint64}", func(context iris.Context) {
		_, _ = context.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("echo is %d", context.Params().GetUint64Default("echo", 0)))
	})

	irisApp.Get("/api/v1/test/{echo:uint64}", func(context iris.Context) {
		_, _ = context.WriteString(fmt.Sprintf("echo 123 is %d", context.Params().GetUint64Default("echo", 0)))
	})

	if err := irisApp.Run(iris.Addr(":8080"), iris.WithCharset("UTF-8")); err != nil {
		logrus.Errorf("error with :%+v", err)
	}
}
```
2. when I use postman to visit 'http://localhost:8080/api/v1/test/123' , it returns 404.

**Expected behavior**
when I visit http://localhost:8080/api/v1/test/123, it should be returns `echo 123 is 123`

**Screenshots**

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: windows or ubuntu

**iris.Version**
- e.g. v12.2.0-beta6

issue.title: How to Graceful Restart the iris project ???
issue.body:
How to Graceful Restart the iris project ???
i know how to graceful restart gin project (use endless)  but not iris

comment.body:
Hello @weijchun,

Whatever works for gin and net/http works for Iris too. 

Take for example, the [endless](https://github.com/fvbock/endless) package you mentioned, it wants an `http.Handler (mux)` on its `endless.ListenAndServe("localhost:4242", mux)` function.

The `app := iris.New()` returns an `*iris.Application` instance, the `*iris.Application` completes the `http.Handler` interface and it's ready to use after `app.Build()`. With Iris, when not calling its `.Listen or .Run` and want to use it as a simple `http.Handler` directly, you need to call its "Build" method because there are many features compared to its alternatives that must be built when routing code is finish. Here's an example of your use case:

```go
app := iris.New()
app.Get("/", func(ctx iris.Context) { ctx.Writef("Hello %s", "Iris") }

if err := app.Build(); err!=nil { // <-
    panic(err)
}

err := endless.ListenAndServe("localhost:4242", app)
```

Simple as that! Have fun!

comment.body:
You can't do this, Application's RegisterView should be called before Listen (= no after build).

You can set multiple view engines [path-based](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L17) or [manually](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L23-L29).

You should not load and render the templates each time dynamically, this will make your app a lot slower. Explain us the problem and we may find a better solution. Also, do the templates written in the disk before server ran or your users upload multiple template files on the fly?

comment.body:
You can't do this, Application's RegisterView should be called before Listen (= no after build).

You can set multiple view engines [path-based](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L17) or [manually](https://github.com/kataras/iris/blob/2adc972bc71813eb1e9f37bbcec9c619a28e1609/_examples/view/context-view-engine/main.go#L23-L29).

You should not load and render the templates each time dynamically, this will make your app a lot slower. Explain us the problem and we may find a better solution.

issue.title: [BUG] Iris server crash with StackOverflow when changing ResponseWriter
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
The Iris server crashes when I attempt to add a NewRelic middleware.

**To Reproduce**
Here is a lightweight reproducible example
```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"net/http"

	"github.com/kataras/golog"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/context"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/middleware/logger"
	"github.com/kataras/iris/v12/middleware/recover"

         "github.com/iris-contrib/middleware/newrelic"
	NR "github.com/newrelic/go-agent/v3/newrelic"
)

func main() {
	app := iris.New()

	// Global middlewares
	app.UseGlobal(recover.New())
	app.UseGlobal(logger.New())
	app.UseGlobal(createNewRelicMiddleware(app.Logger()))

	// Router
	app.Get("/test", test)

	// Start server
	app.Listen(":8080")
}

func test(ctx iris.Context) {
	ctx.Text("Hello world")
}

func createNewRelicMiddleware(logger *golog.Logger) context.Handler {
         appName := "my-app"
	 licenseKey := "enter_key_here"
	// New Relic initialization
	middleware, err := newrelic.New(
		NR.ConfigAppName(appName),
		NR.ConfigLicense(licenseKey),
		NR.ConfigDistributedTracerEnabled(true),
	)
	if err != nil {
		fmt.Println(err)
		logger.Fatal(err)
	}
	return middleware
}
```

**Expected behavior**
Being able to see "Hello World" when I make the HTTP GET request.

**Screenshots**
Here is the console logs 
```

github.com/kataras/iris/v12/context.(*responseWriter).Header(0x0?)
        <autogenerated>:1 +0x2a fp=0xc0206803b0 sp=0xc020680398 pc=0x1589caa
github.com/newrelic/go-agent/v3/newrelic.(*replacementResponseWriter).Header(0x0?)

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**

- Golang 1.19.2 darwin/amd64

**iris.Version**

pull_request.title: Bump github.com/kataras/golog from 0.1.7 to 0.1.8
pull_request.body:
Bumps [github.com/kataras/golog](https://github.com/kataras/golog) from 0.1.7 to 0.1.8.
Release notes

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's releases.

v0.1.8

What's Changed

  • Add func for GetNameForLevel by @​codenamoo in kataras/golog#8
  • copy NewLine value as well when clone logger by @​JayceChant in kataras/golog#9
  • Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 by @​dependabot in kataras/golog#23

New Contributors

  • @​codenamoo made their first contribution in kataras/golog#8
  • @​JayceChant made their first contribution in kataras/golog#9
  • @​dependabot made their first contribution in kataras/golog#23

Full Changelog: https://github.com/kataras/golog/compare/v0.1.7...v0.1.8

Changelog

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's changelog.

Sat 29 October 2022 | v0.1.8

Add golog.Now variable so 3rd-parties can customize the time.Now functionality used in golog.Log.Time and Timestamp.

Wed 09 Decemember | v0.1.6

Fix Clone not inherite the parent's formatters field (fixes SetLevelFormat on childs).

Mo 07 September | v0.1.5

Introduce the Formatter interface. Example.

  • Add Logger.RegisterFormatter(Formatter) to register a custom Formatter.
  • Add Logger.SetFormat(formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to set the default formatter for all log levels.
  • Add Logger.SetLevelFormat(levelName string, formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to change the output format for the given "levelName".

Su 06 September | v0.1.3 and v0.1.4

  • Add Logger.SetLevelOutput(levelName string, w io.Writer) to customize the writer per level.
  • Add Logger.GetLevelOutput(levelName string) io.Writer to get the leveled output or the default one.

Sa 15 August | v0.1.2

  • Logger.Child accepts an interface{} instead of string. This way you can register children for pointers without forcing to naming them. If the key is string or completes the fmt.Stringer interface, then it's used as prefix (like always did).

Fr 14 August 2020 | v0.0.19

  • Use locks on hijacker.

Tu 09 June 2020 | v0.0.18

  • New SetStacktraceLimit method. If 0 (default) all debug stacktrace will be logged, if negative the field is disabled.
  • If TimeFormat field is empty then timestamp field is disabled.

Sa 06 June 2020 | v0.0.16

  • New Fields type that can be passed to Logf/Debugf/Infof/Warnf/Errorf/Fatalf functions and set the Log.Fields data field (which can be retrieved through a custom LogHandler).
  • Add Log.Stacktrace of new Frame type which holds the callers stack trace when Debug/Debugf.
  • Add json struct fields to the Log structure.
  • Update the customize-output example.

Su 17 May 2020 | v0.0.14

Add a Warningf method to complete the dgraph-io/badger.Logger interface and set the Prefix text right before the log's actual message instead of the beginning of the log line.

Tu 28 April 2020 | v0.0.12

This release provides support for colorized log level per registered output. Log's level will be colorful for registered io.Writer(via AddOutput) that supports colors, even when the rest of the writers (e.g. files) don't.

Breaking changes on the Levels map. See the corresponding updated example for migration.

... (truncated)

  • cab8303 release v0.1.8
  • 350ad62 Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 (#23)
  • 5ca7ba3 add dependabot

  • 3ddf6ad Merge pull request #9 from JayceChant/patch-1
  • 687b2b8 Merge branch 'master' into patch-1

pull_request.body:
Bumps [github.com/kataras/golog](https://github.com/kataras/golog) from 0.1.7 to 0.1.8.
Release notes

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's releases.

v0.1.8

What's Changed

  • Add func for GetNameForLevel by @​codenamoo in kataras/golog#8
  • copy NewLine value as well when clone logger by @​JayceChant in kataras/golog#9
  • Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 by @​dependabot in kataras/golog#23

New Contributors

  • @​codenamoo made their first contribution in kataras/golog#8
  • @​JayceChant made their first contribution in kataras/golog#9
  • @​dependabot made their first contribution in kataras/golog#23

Full Changelog: https://github.com/kataras/golog/compare/v0.1.7...v0.1.8

Changelog

Sourced from github.com/kataras/golog's changelog.

Sat 29 October 2022 | v0.1.8

Add golog.Now variable so 3rd-parties can customize the time.Now functionality used in golog.Log.Time and Timestamp.

Wed 09 Decemember | v0.1.6

Fix Clone not inherite the parent's formatters field (fixes SetLevelFormat on childs).

Mo 07 September | v0.1.5

Introduce the Formatter interface. Example.

  • Add Logger.RegisterFormatter(Formatter) to register a custom Formatter.
  • Add Logger.SetFormat(formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to set the default formatter for all log levels.
  • Add Logger.SetLevelFormat(levelName string, formatter string, opts ...interface{}) to change the output format for the given "levelName".

Su 06 September | v0.1.3 and v0.1.4

  • Add Logger.SetLevelOutput(levelName string, w io.Writer) to customize the writer per level.
  • Add Logger.GetLevelOutput(levelName string) io.Writer to get the leveled output or the default one.

Sa 15 August | v0.1.2

  • Logger.Child accepts an interface{} instead of string. This way you can register children for pointers without forcing to naming them. If the key is string or completes the fmt.Stringer interface, then it's used as prefix (like always did).

Fr 14 August 2020 | v0.0.19

  • Use locks on hijacker.

Tu 09 June 2020 | v0.0.18

  • New SetStacktraceLimit method. If 0 (default) all debug stacktrace will be logged, if negative the field is disabled.
  • If TimeFormat field is empty then timestamp field is disabled.

Sa 06 June 2020 | v0.0.16

  • New Fields type that can be passed to Logf/Debugf/Infof/Warnf/Errorf/Fatalf functions and set the Log.Fields data field (which can be retrieved through a custom LogHandler).
  • Add Log.Stacktrace of new Frame type which holds the callers stack trace when Debug/Debugf.
  • Add json struct fields to the Log structure.
  • Update the customize-output example.

Su 17 May 2020 | v0.0.14

Add a Warningf method to complete the dgraph-io/badger.Logger interface and set the Prefix text right before the log's actual message instead of the beginning of the log line.

Tu 28 April 2020 | v0.0.12

This release provides support for colorized log level per registered output. Log's level will be colorful for registered io.Writer(via AddOutput) that supports colors, even when the rest of the writers (e.g. files) don't.

Breaking changes on the Levels map. See the corresponding updated example for migration.

... (truncated)

  • 350ad62 Bump github.com/kataras/pio from 0.0.10 to 0.0.11 (#23)
  • 5ca7ba3 add dependabot
